cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with video frame interpolation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses neural networks for video frame synthesis, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning, cs.MM (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses optical flow algorithms, which are commonly used in computer graphics, cs.GR (Computer Graphics). The paper also involves training a neural network end-to-end, which falls under the sub-category of artificial intelligence, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper uses a state-of-the-art approach, which involves optimization and model selection, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning, cs.LG (Machine Learning).
